    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Ancient Greek visual works comprising pottery objects on which black decoration appears silhouetted on a red ground. Details were incised into the black figures or applied in purple or white pigment. The works gave way to red-figure vase paintings. Works appeared by 720 BCE in Corinth.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079228/Grove Art Online (2008-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000096407/Concise Oxford Dictionary of Art Terms [online] (2001-2008)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Antiche opere visive greche che comprendono oggetti in ceramica su cui appare le decorazioni nera che si stagliano su uno sfondo rosso. I dettagli sono stati incisi nelle figure nere o applicati in pigmento viola o bianco.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Italian</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109543/Italian Term Processing (2020-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Oud-Grieks beeldmateriaal dat bestaat uit pottenbakkersgoed waarop zwarte versieringen in silhouet op een rode ondergrond zijn aangebracht. Details werden in de zwarte figuren gegrift of aangebracht in paars of wit pigment. Later kwamen voor deze werken de roodfigurige vaasschilderingen in de plaats. Deze werken werden voor het eerst gemaakt in 720 v.Chr. in Korinthe.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
